        "id": 1147264
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-04-09T22:26:17Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027m sorry that I don\u0027t have enough context, but I hope I have understood the topic here.\n\nIf the intent of asking Sink to compute and report the most common test ID prefix and var-unions is to reduce the load from server? ResultSink could voluntarily compute provide the most common test ID prefix and variant unions among the test results included, but it means that server won\u0027t verify the correctness the common test ID prefix and var unions.\n\nIf the server has to verify the correctness by computing the common prefix and var unions by itself, then I guess BatchCreateTestResults() wouldn\u0027t have to take the computed values from ResultSink.\n\nOut of curiosity, why couldn\u0027t finalizer iterates all the included tests to compute the most common test id prefix and variant unions? If CreateTestResults() and BatchCreateTestResult() compute the common prefix and var unions, does it mean that the APIs need to update the fields in invocation each time called? Then, we will have to shard the computed values to a separate table, like we do with TestResultcounts.",
      "parentUuid": "952b1611_1187c841",
      "revId": "593f42b5314797c1f24667a0caccccc5390f1c19",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "3617bae4_d818686c",
        "filename": "resultdb/proto/v1/invocation.proto",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 157,
      "author": {
        "id": 1157909
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-04-09T23:23:26Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The idea is that, we pass test_id_prefix and base variants to ResultSink already, so I want ResultSink to pass along those info directly to Invocation. And if those information is good enough for improving the test result history API performance, maybe we don\u0027t even need the pre-computation.\n\n\u003e our database can become inconsistent if someone uploads results bypassing resultSink \n\nGood point. This is a case to prove that we cannot entirely avoid pre-computation...\n\nBut I still think it\u0027s double work for ResultSink to prepend test_id_prefix to all test results it uploads and then in BatchCreateTestResults we iterate all test results to find the common test_id_prefix... (test_result_variant_union OTH is fine since it\u0027s a union.)\n\nHow about this, I don\u0027t touch UpdateInvocation anymore, instead:\n\n1. add common_test_id_prefix to BatchCreateTestResultsRequest,\n2. In BatchCreateTestResults, \n  a. if common_test_id_prefix is specified, Update the invocation\u0027s CommonTestIdPrefix using the longest common prefix of common_test_id_prefix from the request and the invocation\u0027s CommonTestIdPrefix\n  b. if not specified, iterate through test ids to find the new longest common prefix\n3. In CreateTestResults, using the test id and the \nthe invocation\u0027s CommonTestIdPrefix to find the new longest common prefix",
      "parentUuid": "52a47328_8197acb2",
      "revId": "593f42b5314797c1f24667a0caccccc5390f1c19",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "e2824027_db6b6978",
        "filename": "resultdb/proto/v1/invocation.proto",
